/>

<h3>Ref helper</h3>

Creates an object that wraps a value, like a reference, so that it can be gotten and setted. <code>RefInput</code> is a sample input component that is made to handle refs. Final/backwards-compatible API could be considered separately.

<h4>Basic Case</h4>

<pre><code class="language-handlebars">&lt;RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref=&#123;&#123;ref this "inputValue"}}
/&gt;</code></pre>

<RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref={{ref this "inputValue"}}
/>

<h4>Custom Setter</h4>

<pre><code class="language-handlebars">&lt;RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref=&#123;&#123;ref this "inputValue" update=this.trimAndSetInputValue}}
/&gt;</code></pre>

<RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref={{ref this "inputValue" update=this.trimAndSetInputValue}}
/>

<h3>Ref helper (alternate custom setter interface)</h3>

This ref helper's custom setter interface isolates the setter from the context and instead provides it a method for setting the reference. The main benefit here is enabling custom setter helpers that aren't aware of the context.

<h4>Custom setter using helper</h4>

<pre><code class="language-javascript">export default helper(function trimAndSet() {
  return function({ value, set }) {
    set(value.trim());
  };
});</code></pre>

<pre><code class="language-handlebars">&lt;RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref=&#123;&#123;ref2 this "inputValue" update=(trim-and-set)}}
/&gt;</code></pre>

<RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref={{ref2 this "inputValue" update=(trim-and-set)}}
/>

<h4>Custom setter using complex helper</h4>

This is a very silly helper just meant to illustrate the flexibility of this update function interface.

<pre><code class="language-javascript">export default helper(function maybeSetAndNotify([ onSet ]) {
  return function({ oldValue, value, set }) {
    if (value.trim() === oldValue) {
      return;
    }
  
    let toSet;
    if (!value.includes('_')) {
      toSet = value;
    } else {
      toSet = 'invalid input';
    }
  
    set(toSet);
    onSet(toSet);
  };
});</code></pre>

<pre><code class="language-handlebars">&lt;RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref=&#123;&#123;ref2 this "inputValue" update=(maybe-set-and-notify this.onSet)}}
/&gt;</code></pre>

<RefInput
  type="text"
  @ref={{ref2 this "inputValue" update=(maybe-set-and-notify this.onSet)}}
/>

